The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the close in  Buenos
Aires . The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 0.1 percent to 2,304.61.  Central Puerto SA (CEPU2)  (CEPU2 AF) fell 8.9 percent to 12.30
pesos after sliding 10 percent yesterday for the biggest two-day
drop since 2004 The power generator tumbled after reporting a
loss of 6.6 million pesos ($1.5 million) after a profit of 52.3
million pesos a year earlier.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   rallied 2.6 percent to 8.96 pesos.
